OVERVIEW: Manually add or update a product reference for a specific target

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli add-product-reference [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <target-name> [--name <name>] [--type <type>]

ARGUMENTS:
  <target-name>           Name of the target to add product reference to

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  --name <name>           Custom name for the product (optional)
  --type <type>           Product type (e.g.,
                          com.apple.product-type.application)
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

